William F Weld Biography

William F. Weld is the author of the "Boston Globe" bestseller "Mackerel by Moonlight" and of "Big Ugly, " a political satire. He was the governor of Massachusetts from 1991 to 1997 and is a former federal prosecutor. He lives in New York.William F. Weld currently resides in  the state of New York. 




