»



 Bill Weld


 
Actor






Resigned as governor of Massachusetts to be nominated for U.S. Ambassador to Mexico under President Bill Clinton. Nomination was defeated by the U.S. Senate Foreign Affairs Committee under Sen. Jesse Helms, a fellow Republican.            
See full bio »
            
 


Born:

July 31, 
     
1945

            in
            Smithtown, New York, USA










